      "message": "I’ve committed a few local changes and then uploaded with “git cl upload --squash” a few times. “git commit --amend” lets me edit the most recent commit message, but that’s not what Gerrit is using for the whole change’s /COMMIT_MSG.\n\nAm I supposed to git rebase -i to edit the ancestor’s message?",
